01059 void  InitAnimationSurfacesPerBodytype( )
01060 {
01061       INT32 cnt1, cnt2;
01062 
01063       // Should be set to a non-init values
01064       for ( cnt1 = 0; cnt1 < TOTALBODYTYPES; cnt1 ++ )
01065       {
01066             for ( cnt2 = 0; cnt2 < NUMANIMATIONSTATES; cnt2 ++ )
01067             {
01068                   gubAnimSurfaceIndex[ cnt1][ cnt2 ] = INVALID_ANIMATION;
01069                   gubAnimSurfaceItemSubIndex[ cnt1][ cnt2 ] = INVALID_ANIMATION;
01070                   gubAnimSurfaceMidWaterSubIndex[ cnt1][ cnt2 ][ 0 ] = INVALID_ANIMATION;
01071                   gubAnimSurfaceMidWaterSubIndex[ cnt1][ cnt2 ][ 1 ] = INVALID_ANIMATION;
01072                   gubAnimSurfaceCorpseID[ cnt1][ cnt2 ] = NO_CORPSE;
01073             }
01074       }
01075       memset( gRandomAnimDefs, 0, sizeof( gRandomAnimDefs ) );
01076 
01077 
01078       // REGULAR MALE GUY
01079       gubAnimSurfaceIndex[ REGMALE ][ WALKING ]                                           = RGMBASICWALKING;
01080       gubAnimSurfaceIndex[ REGMALE ][ STANDING ]                                          = RGMSTANDING;

03008 BOOLEAN LoadAnimationStateInstructions( )
03009 {
03010             HWFILE            hFile;
03011             UINT32            uiBytesRead;
03012 
03013             // Open ani file
03014             hFile = FileOpen( ANIMFILENAME, FILE_ACCESS_READ, FALSE );
03015 
03016             if ( !hFile )
03017             {
03018                   return( FALSE );
03019             }
03020 
03021             //Read in block
03022             if ( !FileRead( hFile, gusAnimInst, sizeof( gusAnimInst ), &uiBytesRead ) )
03023             {
03024                   return( FALSE );
03025             }
03026 
03027             FileClose( hFile );
03028 
03029             return( TRUE );
03030 }

03032 BOOLEAN IsAnimationValidForBodyType( SOLDIERTYPE *pSoldier, UINT16 usNewState )
03033 {
03034       UINT16            usAnimSurface;
03035 
03036       // From animation control, get surface
03037 
03038       // First Save value
03039       usAnimSurface = DetermineSoldierAnimationSurface( pSoldier, usNewState );
03040 
03041       if ( usAnimSurface == INVALID_ANIMATION_SURFACE )
03042       {
03043             return( FALSE );
03044       }
03045 
03046       return( TRUE );
03047 }
03048 
03049 BOOLEAN SubstituteBodyTypeAnimation( SOLDIERTYPE *pSoldier, UINT16 usTestState, UINT16 *pusSubState )
03050 {
03051       BOOLEAN fSubFound = FALSE;
03052 
03053       *pusSubState = usTestState;
03054 
03055 
03056       if ( pSoldier->ubBodyType == QUEENMONSTER )
03057       {
03058              switch( usTestState )
03059              {
03060                         case STANDING:
03061                         case WALKING:
03062                         case RUNNING:
03063 
03064                               *pusSubState = QUEEN_MONSTER_BREATHING;
03065                               fSubFound = TRUE;
03066                               break;
03067              }
03068       }
03069 
03070       if ( pSoldier->ubBodyType == LARVAE_MONSTER )
03071       {
03072              switch( usTestState )
03073              {
03074                         case STANDING:
03075 
03076                               *pusSubState = LARVAE_BREATH;
03077                               fSubFound = TRUE;
03078                               break;
03079 
03080                         case WALKING:
03081                         case RUNNING:
03082 
03083                               *pusSubState = LARVAE_WALK;
03084                               fSubFound = TRUE;
03085                               break;
03086 
03087              }
03088       }
03089 
03090       if ( pSoldier->ubBodyType == CROW )
03091       {
03092              switch( usTestState )
03093              {
03094                         case WALKING:
03095 
03096                               *pusSubState = CROW_WALK;
03097                               fSubFound = TRUE;
03098                               break;
03099 
03100                         case STANDING:
03101 
03102                               *pusSubState = CROW_EAT;
03103                               fSubFound = TRUE;
03104                               break;
03105 
03106              }
03107       }
03108 
03109       if ( pSoldier->ubBodyType == BLOODCAT )
03110       {
03111              switch( usTestState )
03112              {
03113                         case RUNNING:
03114                               *pusSubState = BLOODCAT_RUN;
03115                               fSubFound = TRUE;
03116                               break;
03117 
03118              }
03119 
03120       }
03121 
03122 
03123       if ( pSoldier->ubBodyType == ADULTFEMALEMONSTER || pSoldier->ubBodyType == AM_MONSTER ||
03124                    pSoldier->ubBodyType == YAF_MONSTER || pSoldier->ubBodyType == YAM_MONSTER )
03125       {
03126              switch( usTestState )
03127              {
03128                         case WALKING:
03129                               *pusSubState = ADULTMONSTER_WALKING;
03130                               fSubFound = TRUE;
03131                               break;
03132 
03133                         case RUNNING:
03134                               *pusSubState = ADULTMONSTER_WALKING;
03135                               fSubFound = TRUE;
03136                               break;
03137 
03138              }
03139       }
03140 
03141       if ( pSoldier->ubBodyType == ROBOTNOWEAPON )
03142       {
03143              switch( usTestState )
03144              {
03145         case STANDING:
03146 
03147           // OK, if they are on the CIV_TEAM, sub for no camera moving
03148           if ( pSoldier->bTeam == CIV_TEAM )
03149           {
03150                                 *pusSubState = ROBOT_CAMERA_NOT_MOVING;
03151                                 fSubFound = TRUE;
03152           }
03153           break;
03154 
03155                         case WALKING:
03156                               *pusSubState = ROBOT_WALK;
03157                               fSubFound = TRUE;
03158                               break;
03159 
03160                         case RUNNING:
03161                               *pusSubState = ROBOT_WALK;
03162                               fSubFound = TRUE;
03163                               break;
03164 
03165              }
03166       }
03167 
03168       if ( IS_CIV_BODY_TYPE( pSoldier ) )
03169       {
03170             switch( usTestState )
03171             {
03172                   case KNEEL_UP:
03173                         *pusSubState = END_COWER;
03174                         fSubFound = TRUE;
03175                         break;
03176                   case KNEEL_DOWN:
03177                         *pusSubState = START_COWER;
03178                         fSubFound = TRUE;
03179                         break;
03180 
03181       case WKAEUP_FROM_SLEEP:
03182       case GOTO_SLEEP:
03183       case SLEEPING:
03184                         *pusSubState = STANDING;
03185                         fSubFound = TRUE;
03186                         break;
03187             }
03188       }
03189 
03190       return( fSubFound );
03191 }

03193 
03194 INT8  GetBodyTypePaletteSubstitutionCode( SOLDIERTYPE *pSoldier, UINT8 ubBodyType, CHAR8 *zColFilename )
03195 {
03196       switch( ubBodyType )
03197       {
03198             case REGMALE:
03199             case BIGMALE:
03200             case STOCKYMALE:
03201             case REGFEMALE:
03202 
03203                   if ( pSoldier != NULL )
03204                   {
03205                         // Are we on fire?
03206                         if ( pSoldier->usAnimState == CHARIOTS_OF_FIRE || pSoldier->usAnimState == BODYEXPLODING )
03207                         {
03208                               return( 0 );
03209                         }
03210 
03211                         
03212                         // Check for camo...
03213                         
03214                         //stealth has priority
03215                         if ( GetWornStealth(pSoldier) >= 50 )
03216                         {
03217                               strcpy( zColFilename, "ANIMS\\stealth.col" );
03218                               return( 1 );
03219                         }
03220                         
03221                         int urban = pSoldier->urbanCamo + pSoldier->wornUrbanCamo;
03222                         int jungle = pSoldier->bCamo + pSoldier->wornCamo;
03223                         int desert = pSoldier->desertCamo + pSoldier->wornDesertCamo;
03224                         int snow = pSoldier->snowCamo + pSoldier->wornSnowCamo;
03225                         int total = urban + jungle + desert + snow;
03226 
03227                         // display camo depending on which is higher
03228                         if ( total >= 50 )
03229                         {
03230                               if ( jungle >= urban && jungle >= desert && jungle >= snow )
03231                                     strcpy( zColFilename, "ANIMS\\camo.COL" );
03232                               else if ( urban >= jungle && urban >= desert && urban >= snow )
03233                                     strcpy( zColFilename, "ANIMS\\urban.col" );
03234                               else if ( desert >= urban && desert >= jungle && desert >= snow )
03235                                     strcpy( zColFilename, "ANIMS\\desert.col" );
03236                               else if ( snow >= urban && snow >= desert && snow >= jungle )
03237                                     strcpy( zColFilename, "ANIMS\\snow.col" );
03238 
03239                               return( 1 );
03240                         }
03241                   }
03242                   return( -1 );
03243 
03244 
03245             case YAF_MONSTER:
03246 
03247                   strcpy( zColFilename, "ANIMS\\MONSTERS\\fm_brite.COL" );
03248                   return( 1 );
03249 
03250             case YAM_MONSTER:
03251 
03252                   strcpy( zColFilename, "ANIMS\\MONSTERS\\mn_brite.COL" );
03253                   return( 1 );
03254 
03255             case ADULTFEMALEMONSTER:
03256                   
03257                   strcpy( zColFilename, "ANIMS\\MONSTERS\\femmon.COL" );
03258                   return( 1 );
03259 
03260             case AM_MONSTER:
03261 
03262                   strcpy( zColFilename, "ANIMS\\MONSTERS\\monster.COL" );
03263                   return( 1 );
03264 
03265             case QUEENMONSTER:
03266             case COW:
03267             case CROW:
03268             case BLOODCAT:
03269             case HUMVEE:
03270             case ELDORADO:
03271             case ICECREAMTRUCK:
03272             case JEEP:
03273             case ROBOTNOWEAPON:
03274             case TANK_NW:
03275             case TANK_NE:
03276 
03277                   return( 0 );
03278       }
03279 
03280       return( -1 );
03281 }

03284 
03285 BOOLEAN SetSoldierAnimationSurface( SOLDIERTYPE *pSoldier, UINT16 usAnimState )
03286 {
03287       UINT16 usAnimSurface;
03288 
03289             // Delete any structure info!
03290       if ( pSoldier->pLevelNode != NULL )
03291       {
03292             DeleteStructureFromWorld( pSoldier->pLevelNode->pStructureData );
03293             pSoldier->pLevelNode->pStructureData = NULL;
03294       }
03295 
03296 
03297       usAnimSurface = LoadSoldierAnimationSurface( pSoldier, usAnimState );
03298 
03299       // Add structure info!
03300       if ( pSoldier->pLevelNode != NULL && !( pSoldier->uiStatusFlags & SOLDIER_PAUSEANIMOVE ) )
03301       {
03302             AddMercStructureInfoFromAnimSurface( pSoldier->sGridNo, pSoldier, usAnimSurface, usAnimState );
03303       }
03304 
03305       // Set
03306       pSoldier->usAnimSurface = usAnimSurface;
03307 
03308       if ( usAnimSurface == INVALID_ANIMATION_SURFACE )
03309       {
03310             return( FALSE );
03311       }
03312 
03313       return( TRUE );
03314 }
03315 
03316 
03317 UINT16 LoadSoldierAnimationSurface( SOLDIERTYPE *pSoldier, UINT16 usAnimState )
03318 {
03319       UINT16 usAnimSurface;
03320 
03321       usAnimSurface = DetermineSoldierAnimationSurface( pSoldier, usAnimState );
03322 
03323       if ( usAnimSurface != INVALID_ANIMATION_SURFACE )
03324       {
03325             // Ensure that it's been loaded!
03326             if ( GetCachedAnimationSurface( pSoldier->ubID, &(pSoldier->AnimCache), usAnimSurface, pSoldier->usAnimState ) == FALSE )
03327             {
03328                   usAnimSurface = INVALID_ANIMATION_SURFACE;
03329             }
03330 
03331       }
03332 
03333       return( usAnimSurface );
03334 }

03336 
03337 UINT16      gusQueenMonsterSpitAnimPerDir[] =
03338 {
03339       QUEENMONSTERSPIT_NE,                //NORTH
03340       QUEENMONSTERSPIT_E,
03341       QUEENMONSTERSPIT_SE,                // EAST
03342       QUEENMONSTERSPIT_S,                       
03343       QUEENMONSTERSPIT_SW,                // SOUTH
03344       QUEENMONSTERSPIT_SW,
03345       QUEENMONSTERSPIT_SW,                // WEST
03346       QUEENMONSTERSPIT_NE,
03347 };
03348 
03349 
03350 UINT16      DetermineSoldierAnimationSurface( SOLDIERTYPE *pSoldier, UINT16 usAnimState )
03351 {
03352       UINT16 usAnimSurface;
03353       UINT16 usAltAnimSurface;
03354       UINT8 ubBodyType;
03355       UINT16      usItem;
03356       UINT8       ubWaterHandIndex = 1;
03357       INT32       cnt;
03358       BOOLEAN     fAdjustedForItem  = FALSE;
03359       UINT16            usNewAnimState;
03360 
03361        //DebugMsg(TOPIC_JA2,DBG_LEVEL_3,String("DetermineSoldierAnimationSurface"));
03362 
03363       ubBodyType = pSoldier->ubBodyType;
03364 
03365       if ( SubstituteBodyTypeAnimation( pSoldier, usAnimState, &usNewAnimState ) )
03366       {
03367             usAnimState = usNewAnimState;
03368       }
03369 
03370       usAnimSurface     =     gubAnimSurfaceIndex[pSoldier->ubBodyType][usAnimState];
03371 
03372       // CHECK IF WE CAN DO THIS ANIMATION, IE WE HAVE IT AVAILIBLE
03373       if ( usAnimSurface == INVALID_ANIMATION   )
03374       {
03375             // WE SHOULD NOT BE USING THIS ANIMATION
03376             ScreenMsg( FONT_MCOLOR_RED, MSG_BETAVERSION, L"Invalid Animation File for Body %d, animation %S.", pSoldier->ubBodyType, gAnimControl[ usAnimState ].zAnimStr );
03377             // Set index to FOUND_INVALID_ANIMATION
03378             gubAnimSurfaceIndex[pSoldier->ubBodyType][usAnimState] = FOUND_INVALID_ANIMATION;
03379             return( INVALID_ANIMATION_SURFACE );
03380       }
03381       if ( usAnimSurface == FOUND_INVALID_ANIMATION   )
03382       {
03383             return( INVALID_ANIMATION_SURFACE );
03384       }
03385 
03386 
03387       // OK - DO SOME MAGIC HERE TO SWITCH BODY TYPES IF WE WANT!
03388 
03389 
03390       // If we are a queen, pick the 'real' anim surface....
03391       if ( usAnimSurface == QUEENMONSTERSPIT_SW )
03392       {
03393             INT8  bDir;
03394 
03395             // Assume a target gridno is here.... get direction...
03396     // ATE: use +2 in gridno because here head is far from body
03397             bDir = (INT8)GetDirectionToGridNoFromGridNo( (INT16)( pSoldier->sGridNo + 2 ), pSoldier->sTargetGridNo );
03398 
03399             return( gusQueenMonsterSpitAnimPerDir[ bDir ] );
03400       }
03401 
03402 
03403       // IF we are not a merc, return
03404       if ( pSoldier->ubBodyType > REGFEMALE )
03405       {
03406             return( usAnimSurface );
03407       }
03408 
03409       // SWITCH TO DIFFERENT AIM ANIMATION FOR BIG GUY!
03410       if ( usAnimSurface == BGMSTANDAIM2 )
03411       {
03412             if ( pSoldier->uiAnimSubFlags & SUB_ANIM_BIGGUYSHOOT2 )
03413             {
03414                   usAnimSurface = BGMSTANDAIM;
03415             }
03416       }
03417 
03418       // SWITCH TO DIFFERENT STAND ANIMATION FOR BIG GUY!
03419       if ( usAnimSurface == BGMSTANDING )
03420       {
03421             if ( pSoldier->uiAnimSubFlags & SUB_ANIM_BIGGUYTHREATENSTANCE )
03422             {
03423                   usAnimSurface = BGMTHREATENSTAND;
03424             }
03425       }
03426 
03427       if ( usAnimSurface == BGMWALKING )
03428       {
03429             if ( pSoldier->uiAnimSubFlags & SUB_ANIM_BIGGUYTHREATENSTANCE )
03430             {
03431                   usAnimSurface = BGMWALK2;
03432             }
03433       }
03434 
03435       if ( usAnimSurface == BGMRUNNING )
03436       {
03437             if ( pSoldier->uiAnimSubFlags & SUB_ANIM_BIGGUYTHREATENSTANCE )
03438             {
03439                   usAnimSurface = BGMRUN2;
03440             }
03441       }
03442 
03443       if ( usAnimSurface == BGMRAISE )
03444       {
03445             if ( pSoldier->uiAnimSubFlags & SUB_ANIM_BIGGUYTHREATENSTANCE )
03446             {
03447                   usAnimSurface = BGMRAISE2;
03448             }
03449       }
03450 
03451 
03452       // ADJUST ANIMATION SURFACE BASED ON TERRAIN
03453 
03454       // CHECK FOR WATER
03455       if ( MercInWater( pSoldier ) )
03456       {
03457 
03458             // ADJUST BASED ON ITEM IN HAND....
03459             usItem = pSoldier->inv[ HANDPOS ].usItem;
03460 
03461             // Default it to the 1 ( ie: no rifle )
03462             if ( usItem != NOTHING )
03463             {
03464                   if ( ( Item[ usItem ].usItemClass == IC_GUN || Item[ usItem ].usItemClass == IC_LAUNCHER ) && !Item[usItem].rocketlauncher)
03465                   {
03466 //                      if ( (Item[ usItem ].fFlags & ITEM_TWO_HANDED) )
03467                         if ( (Item[ usItem ].twohanded ) )
03468                         {
03469                               ubWaterHandIndex = 0;
03470                         }
03471                   }
03472             }
03473 
03474             // CHANGE BASED ON HIEGHT OF WATER
03475             usAltAnimSurface = gubAnimSurfaceMidWaterSubIndex[pSoldier->ubBodyType][usAnimState][ ubWaterHandIndex ];
03476             
03477             if ( usAltAnimSurface != INVALID_ANIMATION )
03478             {
03479                   usAnimSurface = usAltAnimSurface;
03480             }
03481 
03482       }
03483       else
03484       {
03485             // ADJUST BASED ON ITEM IN HAND....
03486             usItem = pSoldier->inv[ HANDPOS ].usItem;
03487 
03488             if ( !(Item[ usItem ].usItemClass == IC_GUN ) && !(Item[ usItem ].usItemClass == IC_LAUNCHER ) || Item[usItem].rocketlauncher )
03489             {
03490                   if ( usAnimState == STANDING )
03491                   {
03492                         usAnimSurface                 = gusNothingBreath[ pSoldier->ubBodyType ];
03493                         fAdjustedForItem  = TRUE;
03494                   }
03495                   else
03496                   {
03497                         usAltAnimSurface = gubAnimSurfaceItemSubIndex[pSoldier->ubBodyType][usAnimState];
03498                         
03499                         if ( usAltAnimSurface != INVALID_ANIMATION )
03500                         {
03501                               usAnimSurface                 = usAltAnimSurface;
03502                               fAdjustedForItem  = TRUE;
03503                         }
03504                   }
03505             }
03506             else
03507             {
03508                   // CHECK FOR HANDGUN
03509                   if ( ( Item[ usItem ].usItemClass == IC_GUN || Item[ usItem ].usItemClass == IC_LAUNCHER ) && !Item[usItem].rocketlauncher )
03510                   {
03511 //                      if ( !(Item[ usItem ].fFlags & ITEM_TWO_HANDED) )
03512                         if ( !(Item[ usItem ].twohanded ) )
03513                         {
03514                               usAltAnimSurface = gubAnimSurfaceItemSubIndex[pSoldier->ubBodyType][usAnimState];
03515                               if ( usAltAnimSurface != INVALID_ANIMATION )
03516                               {
03517                                     usAnimSurface = usAltAnimSurface;
03518                                     fAdjustedForItem  = TRUE;
03519                               }
03520 
03521                               // Look for good two pistols sub anim.....
03522                               if ( gDoubleHandledSub.usAnimState == usAnimState )
03523                               {
03524                                     // Do we carry two pistols...
03525                                     if ( Item[ pSoldier->inv[ SECONDHANDPOS ].usItem ].usItemClass == IC_GUN )
03526                                     {
03527                                           usAnimSurface = gDoubleHandledSub.usAnimationSurfaces[ pSoldier->ubBodyType ];
03528                                           fAdjustedForItem  = TRUE;                                         
03529                                     }
03530                               }
03531 
03532                         }
03533                   }
03534                   else
03535                   {
03536                         usAltAnimSurface = gubAnimSurfaceItemSubIndex[pSoldier->ubBodyType][usAnimState];
03537                         
03538                         if ( usAltAnimSurface != INVALID_ANIMATION )
03539                         {
03540                               usAnimSurface = usAltAnimSurface;
03541                               fAdjustedForItem  = TRUE;
03542                         }
03543                   }
03544             }
03545 
03546             // Based on if we have adjusted for item or not... check for injured status...
03547             if ( fAdjustedForItem )
03548             {
03549                   // If life below thresthold for being injured 
03550                   if ( pSoldier->bLife < INJURED_CHANGE_THREASHOLD )
03551                   {
03552                         // ADJUST FOR INJURED....
03553                         for ( cnt = 0; cnt < NUM_INJURED_SUBS; cnt++ )
03554                         {
03555                               if ( gNothingInjuredSub[ cnt ].usAnimState == usAnimState )
03556                               {
03557                                     usAnimSurface = gNothingInjuredSub[ cnt ].usAnimationSurfaces[ pSoldier->ubBodyType ];
03558                               }
03559                         }
03560                   }
03561             }
03562             else
03563             {
03564                   // If life below thresthold for being injured 
03565                   if ( pSoldier->bLife < INJURED_CHANGE_THREASHOLD )
03566                   {
03567                         // ADJUST FOR INJURED....
03568                         for ( cnt = 0; cnt < NUM_INJURED_SUBS; cnt++ )
03569                         {
03570                               if ( gRifleInjuredSub[ cnt ].usAnimState == usAnimState )
03571                               {
03572                                     usAnimSurface = gRifleInjuredSub[ cnt ].usAnimationSurfaces[ pSoldier->ubBodyType ];
03573                               }
03574                         }
03575                   }
03576             }
03577 
03578 
03579 
03580       }
03581        //DebugMsg(TOPIC_JA2,DBG_LEVEL_3,String("DetermineSoldierAnimationSurface done"));
03582       return( usAnimSurface );
03583 }

03587 {
03588       UINT16 usAnimSurface;
03589 
03590       usAnimSurface = pSoldier->usAnimSurface;
03591 
03592       if ( usAnimSurface != INVALID_ANIMATION_SURFACE )
03593       {
03594             // Ensure that it's loaded!
03595             if ( gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usAnimSurface ].hVideoObject == NULL )
03596             {
03597                   ScreenMsg( FONT_MCOLOR_RED, MSG_BETAVERSION, L"IAnimation Surface for Body %d, animation %S, surface %d not loaded.", pSoldier->ubBodyType, gAnimControl[ usAnimState ].zAnimStr, usAnimSurface );          
03598       AnimDebugMsg( String( "Surface Database: PROBLEMS!!!!!!" ) );
03599       usAnimSurface = INVALID_ANIMATION_SURFACE;
03600             }
03601       }
03602
